          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to format a numeric input by padding it with leading zeros to achieve a specified total length. This function is useful in scenarios where consistent formatting of numbers is required, such as generating fixed-length identifiers or codes."
